{"id":"holomush-gk8b.29","title":"Migration equivalence test silently skips assertions on documented divergences","description":"In internal/access/migration_equivalence_test.go, when a test case has a non-empty 'comment' field (documented divergence), the test logs the divergence but never asserts anything. This means a regression where the new engine makes a wrong decision in the documented-divergence cases goes completely undetected.

