{"id":"holomush-0hag.5","title":"PlayerMessage missing suffix match for entity-scoped _ACCESS_DENIED codes","description":"In internal/command/errors.go, PlayerMessage() adds suffix matching for _ACCESS_EVALUATION_FAILED (line ~162) but does NOT add corresponding suffix matching for _ACCESS_DENIED. The world service's checkAccess() helper (internal/world/service.go:91) generates entity-scoped denial codes like LOCATION_ACCESS_DENIED, EXIT_ACCESS_DENIED, CHARACTER_ACCESS_DENIED, SCENE_ACCESS_DENIED, OBJECT_ACCESS_DENIED, and EXAMINE_ACCESS_DENIED. These codes do NOT match the exact CodePermissionDenied ("PERMISSION_DENIED") case in the switch statement, so they all fall through to the default case returning "Something went wrong. Try again." instead of "You don't have permission to do that."

