{"id":"holomush-wfza.17","title":"gosec G101 suppressed globally for all test files","description":"The .golangci.yaml change at lines 102-106 adds a global gosec G101 suppression for all *_test.go files with the comment 'Test password hashes are not real credentials.'

The suppression targets the specific string pattern matching G101 ('G101') but has no text: filter scoped to the actual hash pattern — it silences every G101 hit across all test files. This could mask genuine accidental credential leaks in test fixtures other than password-hashing tests (e.g., API keys, tokens, real DB passwords accidentally committed to test files).

